As the world is still attempting to adjust itself after the halt of sporting events due to the coronavirus outbreak, Ronaldinho hasn’t kept himself down. Ronaldinho is behind bars after he was arrested attempting to enter Paraguay with an adulterated passport in early March. The 2005 Ballon d’Or winner celebrated his 40th birthday on March 21 inside the prison with his older brother, Roberto Assis, who is also spending time with him for the same crime. And now, a video has surfaced from the Paraguayan prison, showing the World Cup-winner taking part in a game of foot-volleyball with other inmates.   